comments: Ecliptic at the standard reference epoch
X-Y plane: adopted Earth orbital plane at the reference epoch
Note: obliquity of 84381.448 arcseconds (IAU76) wrt ICRF equator
Z-axis   : perpendicular to the X-Y plane in the directional (+ or -) sense
of Earth's north pole at the reference epoch.
Symbol meaning [1 au= 149597870.700 km, 1 day= 86400.0 s]
JD     Julian day number, barycentric dynamical time
IN     Inclination w.r.t X-Y plane, i (degrees)
OM     Longitude of Ascending Node, OMEGA, (degrees)
Tp     Time of periapsis (Julian Day Number)
Geometric states/elements have no aberrations applied
ra   right ascension of axis of rotation
dec  declination of axis of rotation
